  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Direct Assistance for Victims of Trafficking (VOTs) in Nigeria through a Victim Centred Approach</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at improving referral mechanisms and services enhancing protection of victims of trafficking (VoT). IOM will develop standardized screening tools based on a victim-centred approach. The enhanced identification process will be rolled out in four states with a high incidence of human trafficking and along points of entry and exit. IOM will facilitate coordination meetings among stakeholders to share best practices and lessons learnt on the referral process of VoTs to strengthen future.</narrative>
  </description>
